%T A394316 12849984223976516280060,191124940391507029956354672,
%U A394316 2849103046985039826629078767336,42431068357664514158185757533903016,632123705535308549828169755472949280284,9415951212324413613845753459413274639950172
%N A394316 Number of Hamiltonian cycles on a simple grid graph of size 4 X 4 X n.
%C A394316 Computed using Algorithm E in TAOCP Fasc 8a and cross-checked for the first three terms by brute force and for the first four terms using Algorithm H in TAOCP Fasc 8a.
%C A394316 The cycles are undirected. Clockwise and counterclockwise are counted as the same.
%C A394316 No reduction is made for symmetries of the cuboid (or the cube). Rotating or reflecting a Hamiltonian cycle counts as distinct.
%H A394316 Donald E. Knuth, <a href="https://www-cs-faculty.stanford.edu/~knuth/fasc8a.pdf">The Art of Computer Programming, Pre-fascicle 8a, Hamiltonian paths and cycles</a>.
%e A394316 a(1) = 6 because there are 6 Hamiltonian cycles on a 4 X 4 X 1 grid graph (namely, four that are U-shaped and two that are H-shaped).
%Y A394316 Cf. A003763, A193346, A003699.
%K A394316 nonn,hard,more,new
